hello internetty it has occurred to me that digital world perception has skewed and screwed yet again 🎭 I recently went to a social gathering and experienced the same exchange over and over— before properly getting into a convo they tell me my life looks great and things seem to be going well, regurgitating tidbits i’ve shared to the internet. onward. all in all, they are, good things have been happening to me, and work of all kinds has been paying off. I am SO grateful. but I hear that sliver of my reality being projected and it makes my heart sink, because of c it’s not even close to my full human experience (I know we are associated with our insta g selves but idk it hit different). with clients and friends we can really get into it, but I left this gathering reeling and feeling really fucked up because overall I have not been okay. my emotional & mental health have been hella unstable with a riveting anxious baseline. I am going through some things that I have never experienced and it has my nerves shot round the clock. I am sharing this not to elicit sympathy or advice (although to neither I am averse); I do have a small but solid network of people I feel held by, but am posting this to remind myself and others that folks are not their internet or passing presence. I withhold details of my anxieties & tribulations to secure autonomy and professionalism on this platform but I too am human! Drawing for me is hours of pure solitude, and tattooing is that shared with one other person, so instagram can be a great tool to help communicate at times. Being present for each other in any ~real~ way can really flip the script you know?? I know so many people have been going through it. I just feel like it helps me when I see others share their dark faucets so I hope maybe this helps a little too 🌀🔁 here’s a drawing I finished in the middle of the night, collab w my past self

teeny fighter

I sat down and drew this til it was finished, a new year reflection. it’s been so hard to draw lately!! with all that is happening. in this world, in life, in the year, the season, the day. in asheville ahaha. I thought about how I grew up being mean, without intending to… telling people how to adjust their attitude because I saw it rude or embarrassing, out of line of manners, and learned how that is how people are, and that is actually what makes us so unique and charming. we are all different and it’s those little things that drive us crazy, but also crazy in love. with each other! and I love that. I reflect on this today because my mom just shared how she is unlearning this too :,) I hope this year makes way for kindness, and forgiveness, and understanding, even if we don’t quite understand. grace I guess!!! I hope we can give each other a break. and I really hope that we can make space for newness in each other because we are all growing so so so much. I hope to bring and share love and give each other a million chances in this life. goodbye grudges I hope to let this ego lie a little more deeply this year 💧
